725616f-a.title: Queens: 73rd Avenue - 179th Street
725616f-a.text:
73rd Avenue, north side, at 179th Street, showing the
colonial Brinkerhoff House, built about 1700. The farm,
which comprised 38 acres in 1891, was owned by Hoagland
(1860), J. Diehl (1873), and Schleider (1891-1900). The
avenue was formely named Plack Stump Road.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1926
MAY BE REPRODUCED  Views 1,2,3

725613f-b.title: Queens: 73rd Avenue - 179th Street
725613f-b.text:
73rd Avenue, north side, at 179th Street, showing the
old Brinkerhoff Homestead, built about 1700. Later it was
known as the Skidmore house and also the J. Diehl house.
The latter owned it in 1873. In 1891-1909 it was on the
38-acre farm of Schleider.
P. 1  . Sperr  Views 1,2: March 31, 1927
NO RAPRODUCTIONS
